th Popcount-Depth Equal to K II use?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"It primarily maps to fenwick tree, within the broader topic of math.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Is Number of Integers With Popcount-Depth Equal to K II good for interviews?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes — as a Hard problem it is a solid practice target. Pair it with related problems in the same pattern family for spaced repetition.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Where can I read the official statement?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Open the official LeetCode page for constraints and examples: https://leetcode.com/problems/number-of-integers-with-popcount-depth-equal-to-k-ii/\"}}]}0:{\"rsc\":[\"$\",\"$1\",\"c\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"container-af py-8\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Article\\\",\\\"headline\\\":\\\"Number of Integers With Popcount-Depth Equal to K II\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Original Hard explanation for Number of Integers With Popcount-Depth Equal to K II (LeetCode #3624). Pattern: fenwick tree. Time precompute: O((logr) * log(logr)) runtime: O(nlogr + maxk * n + nlogn + qlogn), space O(logr + maxk * n). Multi-language solutions and interview tips.\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://algoforge.dev/problems/number-of-integers-with-popcount-depth-equal-to-k-ii\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Organization\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"AlgoForge\\\"},\\\"publisher\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Organization\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"AlgoForge\\\"},\\\"datePublished\\\":\\\"2026-01-01\\\",\\\"dateModified\\\":\\\"2026-07-17\\\"}\"}}],[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$2\"}}],[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowTo\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"How to solve Number of Integers With Popcount-Depth Equal to K II\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Original Hard explanation for Number of Integers With Popcount-Depth Equal to K II (LeetCode #3624). Pattern: fenwick tree. Time precompute: O((logr) * log(logr)) runtime: O(nlogr + maxk * n + nlogn + qlogn), space O(logr + maxk * n). Multi-language solutions and interview tips.\\\",\\\"step\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":1,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Read the official problem statement on LeetCode\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":2,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Solve on paper / whiteboard first\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":3,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Implement the fenwick tree approach\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":4,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Verify edge cases from the checklist\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":5,\\\"text\\\":\\\"State time and space complexity aloud\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":6,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Compare with the AlgoForge reference solution\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":7,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Schedule a revision session\\\"}]}\"}}],[\"$\",\"nav\",null,{\"aria-label\":\"Breadcrumb\",\"className\":\"text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":[\"$L3\",\"$L4\"]}],\"$L5\"]}],[\"$L6\"],\"$L7\"]}],\"isPartial\":false,\"staleTime\":300,\"varyParams\":null,\"buildId\":\"qYmpHdIWGSv0ZBoY8Y0Bn\"}\n3:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\",\\\"itemListElement\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":1,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Home\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://algoforge.dev/\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":2,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Problems\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://algoforge.dev/problems\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":3,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Number of Integers With Popcount-Depth Equal to K II\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://algoforge.dev/problems/number-of-integers-with-popcount-depth-equal-to-k-ii\\\"}]}\"}}]\n4:[\"$\",\"ol\",null,{\"className\":\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-1.5\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"li\",\"/\",{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-1.5\",\"children\":[false,[\"$\",\"$L8\",null,{\"href\":\"/\",\"className\":\"hover:text-primary transition-colors\",\"children\":\"Home\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"/problems\",{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-1.5\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"aria-hidden\":true,\"className\":\"text-border\",\"children\":\"/\"}],[\"$\",\"$L8\",null,{\"href\":\"/problems\",\"className\":\"hover:text-primary transition-colors\",\"children\":\"Problems\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"/problems/number-of-integers-with-popcount-depth-equal-to-k-ii\",{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-1.5\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"aria-hidden\":true,\"className\":\"text-border\",\"children\":\"/\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-foreground font-medium\",\"aria-current\":\"page\",\"children\":\"Number of Integers With Popcount-Depth Equal to K II\"}]]}]]}]\nb:T906,// Time:  precompute: O((logr) * log(logr) + log*(r) * (logr)) = O((logr) * log(logr)), r = max(n)\n//        runtime:    O(nlogr + max_k * n + nlogn + qlogn)\n// Space: O(logr + max_k * n)\n\n// fenwick tree\nclass BIT {\npublic:\n    BIT(int n) : bit_(n + 1) {  // 0-indexed\n    }\n    \n    void add(int i, int val) {\n        ++i;\n        for (; i < size(bit_); i += lower_bit(i)) {\n            bit_[i] += val;\n        }\n    }\n\n    int query(int i) const {\n        ++i;\n        int total = 0;\n        for (; i > 0; i -= lower_bit(i)) {\n            total += bit_[i];\n        }\n        return total;\n    }\n\nprivate:\n    int lower_bit(int i) const {\n        return i & -i;\n    }\n    \n    vector<int> bit_;\n};\n\nint bit_length(int64_t x) {\n    return (x ? std::__lg(x) : -1) + 1;\n}\n\nint ceil_log2(int64_t x) {\n    return std::__lg(x - 1) + 1;\n};\n\npair<vector<int>, int> init() {\n    int64_t MAX_N = 1e15;\n    static const int MAX_BIT_LEN = bit_length(MAX_N);\n    vector<int> D(MAX_BIT_LEN + 1, 0);\n    for (int i = 2; i < size(D); ++i) {\n        D[i] = D[__builtin_popcount(i)] + 1;\n    }\n    int MAX_K = 0;\n    for (; MAX_N != 1; ++MAX_K) {  // O(log*(MAX_N)) times\n        MAX_N = ceil_log2(MAX_N);\n    }\n    return {D, MAX_K};\n}\n\nconst auto& [D, MAX_K] = init();\nclass Solution {\npublic:\n    vector<int> popcountDepth(vector<long long>& nums, vector<vector<long long>>& queries) {\n        const auto& count = [](int64_t x) {\n            return x != 1 ? D[__builtin_popcountll(x)] + 1 : 0;\n        };\n\n        vector<BIT> bit(MAX_K + 1, BIT(size(nums)));\n        for (int i = 0; i < size(nums); ++i) {\n            bit[count(nums[i])].add(i, +1);\n        }\n        vector<int> result;\n        for (const auto& q : queries) {\n            if (q[0] == 1) {\n                const int l = q[1], r = q[2], k = q[3];\n                assert(k < size(bit));\n                result.emplace_back(bit[k].query(r) - bit[k].query(l - 1));\n            } else {\n                const auto& i = q[1], &x = q[2];\n                const auto& old_d = count(nums[i]);\n                const auto& new_d = count(x);\n                if (new_d != old_d) {\n                    bit[old_d].add(i, -1);\n                    bit[new_d].add(i, +1);\n                }\n                nums[i] = x;\n            }\n        }\n        return result;\n    }\n};\nc:T76c,# Time:  precompute: O((logr) * log(logr) + log*(r) * (logr)) = O((logr) * log(logr)), r = max(n)\n#        runtime:    O(nlogr + max_k * n + nlogn + qlogn)\n# Space: O(logr + max_k * n)\n\n# fenwick tree\ndef popcount(x):\n    return bin(x).count('1')\n\n\ndef ceil_log2(x):\n    return (x-1).bit_length()\n\n\nclass BIT(object):  # 0-indexed.\n    def __init__(self, n):\n        self.__bit = [0]*(n+1)  # Extra one for dummy node.\n\n    def add(self, i, val):\n        i += 1  # Extra one for dummy node.\n        while i < len(self.__bit):\n            self.__bit[i] += val\n            i += (i & -i)\n\n    def query(self, i):\n        i += 1  # Extra one for dummy node.\n        ret = 0\n        while i > 0:\n            ret += self.__bit[i]\n            i -= (i & -i)\n        return ret\n\n\nMAX_N = 10**15\nMAX_BIT_LEN = MAX_N.bit_length()\nD = [0]*(MAX_BIT_LEN+1)\nfor i in xrange(2, MAX_BIT_LEN+1):\n    D[i] = D[popcount(i)]+1\nMAX_K = 0\nwhile MAX_N != 1:  # O(log*(MAX_N)) times\n    MAX_N = ceil_log2(MAX_N)\n    MAX_K += 1\nclass Solution(object):\n    def popcountDepth(self, nums, queries):\n        \"\"\"\n        :type nums: List[int]\n        :type queries: List[List[int]]\n        :rtype: List[int]\n        \"\"\"\n        def count(x):\n            return D[popcount(x)]+1 if x != 1 else 0\n        \n        bit = [BIT(len(nums)) for _ in xrange(MAX_K+1)]\n        for i in xrange(len(nums)):\n            bit[count(nums[i])].add(i, +1)\n        result = []\n        for q in queries:\n            if q[0] == 1:\n                _, l, r, k = q\n                assert(k < len(bit))\n                result.append(bit[k].query(r)-bit[k].query(l-1))\n            else:\n                _, i, x = q\n                old_d = count(nums[i])\n                new_d = count(x)\n                if new_d != old_d:\n                    bit[old_d].add(i, -1)\n                    bit[new_d].add(i, +1)\n                nums[i] = x\n        return result\n5:[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-6 grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_280px] gap-10\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"article\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"header\",null,{\"className\":\"space-y-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm text-muted-foreground tabular-nums\",\"children\":[\"#\",3624]}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide bg-hard/15 text-hard\",\"children\":\"Hard\"}],false,[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":[\"~\",50,\" min\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"h1\",null,{\"className\":\"text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight\",\"children\":\"Number of Integers With Popcount-Depth Equal to K II\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-muted-foreground max-w-2xl\",\"children\":[\"Time \",[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"className\":\"text-foreground\",\"children\":\"precompute: O((logr) * log(logr)) runtime: O(nlogr + maxk * n + nlogn + qlogn)\"}],\" · \",\"Space \",[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"className\":\"text-foreground\",\"children\":\"O(logr + maxk * n)\"}],\" · \",[\"$\",\"a\",null,{\"href\":\"https://leetcode.com/problems/number-of-integers-with-popcount-depth-equal-to-k-ii/\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"text-primary underline-offset-2 hover:underline\",\"children\":\"Official statement on LeetCode\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex flex-wrap gap-2\",\"children\":[[[\"$\",\"$L8\",\"math\",{\"href\":\"/topics/math\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide bg-primary/15 text-primary\",\"children\":\"math\"}]}]],[[\"$\",\"$L8\",\"fenwick-tree\",{\"href\":\"/patterns/fenwick-tree\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"fenwick tree\"}]}]],[]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex flex-wrap gap-2 pt-1\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L9\",null,{\"slug\":\"number-of-integers-with-popcount-depth-equal-to-k-ii\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L8\",\"cpp\",{\"href\":\"/problems/number-of-integers-with-popcount-depth-equal-to-k-ii/cpp\",\"className\":\"text-sm text-primary hover:underline\",\"children\":\"cpp\"}],[\"$\",\"$L8\",\"python\",{\"href\":\"/problems/number-of-integers-with-popcount-depth-equal-to-k-ii/python\",\"className\":\"text-sm text-primary hover:underline\",\"children\":\"python\"}]]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-10\",\"id\":\"solutions\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold mb-3\",\"children\":\"Solutions\"}],[\"$\",\"$La\",null,{\"solutions\":{\"cpp\":{\"language\":\"C++\",\"languageSlug\":\"cpp\",\"filename\":\"number-of-integers-with-popcount-depth-equal-to-k-ii.cpp\",\"code\":\"$b\",\"sourcePath\":\"C++/number-of-integers-with-popcount-depth-equal-to-k-ii.cpp\"},\"python\":{\"language\":\"Python\",\"languageSlug\":\"python\",\"filename\":\"number-of-integers-with-popcount-depth-equal-to-k-ii.py\",\"code\":\"$c\",\"sourcePath\":\"Python/number-of-integers-with-popcount-depth-equal-to-k-ii.py\"}}}]]}],[\"$Ld\",\"$Le\",\"$Lf\",\"$L10\",\"$L11\",\"$L12\",\"$L13\",\"$L14\",\"$L15\",\"$L16\"],\"$L17\",\"$L18\",\"$L19\",\"$L1a\",\"$L1b\",\"$L1c\"]}],\"$L1d\"]}]\n6:[\"$\",\"script\",\"script-0\",{\"src\":\"/_next/static/chunks/259rkrk9l2f9c.js\",\"async\":true}]\n7:[\"$\",\"$L1e\",null,{\"children\":[\"$\",\"$1f\",null,{\"name\":\"Next.MetadataOutlet\",\"children\":\"$@20\"}]}]\n21:T428,<h2>What is Number of Integers With Popcount-Depth Equal to K II?</h2>\n<p><strong>Number of Integers With Popcount-Depth Equal to K II</strong> (LeetCode #3624) is a <strong>Hard</strong> problem that primarily trains <strong>math</strong>.</p>\n<h3>How to think about it</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Restate the goal</strong> in your own words before coding.</li>\n<li>Work a <strong>tiny example</strong> by hand so the invariant becomes obvious.</li>\n<li>Identify the <strong>pattern</strong> — this problem aligns with <strong>fenwick tree</strong>.</li>\n<li>Only then translate the idea into code.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Why this problem matters</h3>\n<p>Hard problems force you to combine patterns and prove complexity carefully — interview gold.\nOfficial solution notes mention: BIT, Fenwick Tree.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>AlgoForge explanations are original teaching notes. Always open the <a href=\"https://leetcode.com/problems/number-of-integers-with-popcount-depth-equal-to-k-ii/\">official problem statement on LeetCode</a> for constraints and examples.</p>\n</blockquote>\nd:[\"$\",\"section\",\"beginner\",{\"id\":\"beginner\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Beginner Explanation\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$21\"}}]]}]\n22:T52b,<h2>Interview approach for Number of Integers With Popcount-Depth Equal to K II</h2>\n<h3>Opening (30–60 seconds)</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Clarify inputs/outputs and edge cases (empty input, single element, duplicates, overflow).</li>\n<li>State a <strong>brute force</strong> so the interviewer knows you can solve it naively.</li>\n<li>Propose the <strong>optimal direction</strong> tied to <strong>fenwick tree</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Core solution narrative</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Define the <strong>state</strong> you track (pointers, DP cell, set membership, stack top, etc.).</li>\n<li>Explain the <strong>transition</strong> when you process the next element.</li>\n<li>Call out <strong>time</strong> (precompute: O((logr) * log(logr)) runtime: O(nlogr + maxk * n + nlogn + qlogn)) and <strong>space</strong> (O(logr + maxk * n)) before coding.</li>\n<li>Code cleanly; narrate variable names.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>What interviewers listen for</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Correctness on edge cases</li>\n<li>Complexity honesty</li>\n<li>Ability to discuss <strong>trade-offs</strong> (e.g., hash map space vs. sort + two pointers)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Follow-up questions they may ask</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Can you solve it with less memory?</li>\n<li>What if the input stream is infinite / doesn't fit in RAM?</li>\n<li>How would tests look for adversarial inputs?</li>\n</ul>\ne:[\"$\",\"section\",\"interview\",{\"id\":\"interview\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Interview Walkthrough\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$22\"}}]]}]\nf:[\"$\",\"section\",\"optimized\",{\"id\":\"optimized\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Optimized Approach\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Optimized solution notes</h2>\\n<p>The reference solutions on AlgoForge target <strong>precompute: O((logr) * log(logr)) runtime: O(nlogr + maxk * n + nlogn + qlogn)</strong> time and <strong>O(logr + maxk * n)</strong> space.</p>\\n<h3>Pattern focus: fenwick tree</h3>\\n<p>Use the pattern as a checklist:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>fenwick tree</strong> — confirm the invariant holds after each step</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>Multiple methods appear in the source solutions — compare them and explain when each is preferable.</p>\\n<h3>Implementation tips</h3>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Prefer readable names over micro-optimizations in interviews.</li>\\n<li>Extract helpers only when they clarify (e.g., expand-around-center, DFS visit).</li>\\n<li>After AC-level logic, re-scan for off-by-one and null checks.</li>\\n</ul>\\n\"}}]]}]\n10:[\"$\",\"section\",\"complexity\",{\"id\":\"complexity\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Complexity Analysis\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Complexity</h2>\\n<table>\\n<thead>\\n<tr>\\n<th>Measure</th>\\n<th>Bound</th>\\n</tr>\\n</thead>\\n<tbody>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Time</td>\\n<td><strong>precompute: O((logr) * log(logr)) runtime: O(nlogr + maxk * n + nlogn + qlogn)</strong></td>\\n</tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Space</td>\\n<td><strong>O(logr + maxk * n)</strong></td>\\n</tr>\\n</tbody>\\n</table>\\n<h3>How to justify this in an interview</h3>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Time:</strong> count loops, map/set operations, and recursive branching; state average vs worst case if relevant.</li>\\n<li><strong>Space:</strong> include hash maps, recursion stack, and output allocation when the problem asks for it.</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>If your implementation differs from the reference, re-derive big-O from <em>your</em> code — never memorize a complexity you cannot defend.</p>\\n\"}}]]}]\n11:[\"$\",\"section\",\"common-mistakes\",{\"id\":\"common-mistakes\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Common Mistakes\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Common mistakes on Number of Integers With Popcount-Depth Equal to K II</h2>\\n<ol>\\n<li><strong>Skipping edge cases</strong> — empty collections, single-element inputs, max constraints.</li>\\n<li><strong>Wrong invariant</strong> for fenwick tree — updating state too early or too late.</li>\\n<li><strong>Mutating input unexpectedly</strong> when the problem forbids it.</li>\\n<li><strong>Off-by-one</strong> in windows, ranges, or binary search bounds.</li>\\n<li><strong>Ignoring overflow / precision</strong> for integer arithmetic problems.</li>\\n<li><strong>Overengineering</strong> — jumping to an advanced structure when a simpler approach works.</li>\\n</ol>\\n\"}}]]}]\n12:[\"$\",\"section\",\"alternatives\",{\"id\":\"alternatives\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Alternative Approaches\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Alternatives</h2>\\n<p>The source file includes more than one method. Compare:</p>\\n<ol>\\n<li><strong>Primary optimized path</strong> — best complexity for typical interviews.</li>\\n<li><strong>Secondary approach</strong> — often brute force, sorting-based, or space-optimized variant.</li>\\n</ol>\\n<p>Practice articulating <strong>when</strong> you would pick each (constraints, readability, follow-ups).</p>\\n\"}}]]}]\n13:[\"$\",\"section\",\"edge-cases\",{\"id\":\"edge-cases\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Edge Cases\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Edge cases checklist</h2>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Minimum input size</li>\\n<li>Maximum input size / time limits</li>\\n<li>Duplicates and already-sorted input</li>\\n<li>Negative numbers / zeros (if applicable)</li>\\n<li>Disconnected structures (graphs/trees)</li>\\n<li>Single path vs branching recursion depth</li>\\n</ul>\\n\"}}]]}]\n14:[\"$\",\"section\",\"pattern-recognition\",{\"id\":\"pattern-recognition\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Pattern Recognition\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Spotting this pattern</h2>\\n<p>Signal phrases that point to <strong>fenwick tree</strong>:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Sorted input or ability to sort without changing the answer class</li>\\n<li>Need for contiguous subarray / substring → consider sliding window</li>\\n<li>Need for O(1) membership → hash set/map</li>\\n<li>Optimal substructure + overlapping subproblems → DP</li>\\n<li>Connectivity / components → graph DFS/BFS or Union-Find</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>Primary topics: <strong>math</strong>.</p>\\n\"}}]]}]\n15:[\"$\",\"section\",\"follow-ups\",{\"id\":\"follow-ups\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Follow-up Interview Questions\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Follow-ups</h2>\\n<ol>\\n<li>How does the solution change if the input is a stream?</li>\\n<li>Can you solve it in-place?</li>\\n<li>What if duplicates must be handled differently?</li>\\n<li>How would you parallelize the approach?</li>\\n<li>Design tests that would break a buggy implementation.</li>\\n</ol>\\n\"}}]]}]\n16:[\"$\",\"section\",\"practice\",{\"id\":\"practice\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Practice Recommendations\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>What to practice next</h2>\\n<ol>\\n<li>Re-solve <strong>Number of Integers With Popcount-Depth Equal to K II</strong> in a second language (cpp, python).</li>\\n<li>Drill 3–5 more problems tagged <strong>math</strong>.</li>\\n<li>Teach the